quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  11,84,"To Midian [God sent] their brother Shuayb. He said: \"My people, worship God [Alone]! You have no other deity except Him. Do not give short measure and weight. I see you enjoy well-being while I fear the torment of an overpowering day for you"
  11,85,"My people, give full measure and weight with all fairness, and do not cheat men of their belongings nor cause havoc on earth as mischief makers do"
  11,86,Anything God leaves over is best for you provided you believe. I am no guardian set up over you
  11,87,"They said: \"Shuayb, does your prayer command you that we must abandon what our forefathers worshipped, or that we should [not] do what we wish to with our property? Yet you are such a lenient, normal person"
  11,88,"He said: \"My people, have you considered whether I bear any explanation from my Lord? He has provided me with handsome sustenance from Himself. I do not want to oppose you in what I am forbidding you; I only want to improve matters so far as I can manage to. My success lies only with God; on Him have I relied and to Him do I refer"
  11,89,"My people, let not disagreement with me involve you in any crime, so the same fate as struck Noah´s folk, or Hud´s folk or Salih´s folk, will strike you. Lot´s folk even lived not far away from you"
  11,90,"Seek forgiveness from your Lord; then turn towards Him; my Lord is Merciful, Affectionate"
  11,91,"They said; \"Shuayb, we do not understand most of what you say. We do see you are weak compared to us, and were it not for your immediate family, we´d expel you. You are not so dear to us"
  11,92,"He said: \"My folk, are my family ties dearer to you than God is? You thrust Him behind you, turning your backs on Him! Yet my Lord embraces anything you do"
  11,93,"My people, do anything that lies within your power; I am (likewise) acting. You will soon know who will be brought torment which will disgrace him, and who is lying. Watch out! I am watching along with you"
  11,94,"When Our command came, We saved Shuayb and those who believed with him through mercy from Ourself, while the Blast overtook those who had been doing wrong, so they lay cowering in their homes one morning"
  11,95,"just as if they had never prospered there. Was it not away with Midian, just as Thamud was also sent away"